<h2>Employment Opportunities</h2>




<p>The following research and employment opportunities at
NASA's Goddard Institute for Space Studies
are announced:</p>







<p style=" text-indent: -1em; margin-left: 1em;">+
   <a href="columbia_20240416.html">
   Columbia University,
   Postdoctoral Research Scientist in Arctic Climate Study</a><br />
   (Posted 2024-04-16; closes when filled)</p>



<p style=" text-indent: -1em; margin-left: 1em;">+
   <a href="columbia_20240201.html">
   Columbia University,
   Associate Research Scientist in Atmospheric Modeling and Machine Learning</a><br />
   (Posted 2024-02-01; closes when filled)</p>













<p>
Following are links to general information about potential employment at NASA GISS.
</p>

<h4>NASA Employment</h4>

<p>
Announcements of NASA civil service openings (both science and administrative staff)
at NASA GISS
are posted to the
<a href="http://www.usajobs.gov/">USA Jobs</a> website, and reposted here.
</p>




<h4>Postdoctoral Research</h4>

<p>In addition to specific opportunities that may be announced above,
postdoctoral research openings at NASA GISS are ongoing through the
Oak Ridge Associated Universities NASA Postdoctoral Program (ORAU-NPP),
Columbia University Climate School Postdoctoral Program,
and others.<br />
<a href="postdoc.html">+ Read More</a></p>



<h4>University Research Staff</h4>

<p>
Opportunities for postdoctoral science appointments, associate research scientists, and research support positions at NASA GISS that are offered through Columbia University but not listed above should be announced on the university's academic recruitment website.
Enter "Goddard Institute" or "Center for Climate Systems Research" as keywords in that site's job descriptions search form.<br />
<a href="https://academic.careers.columbia.edu/">+ Go to Website</a>
</p>



<h4>Contract Support</h4>

<p>For information regarding potential computer programming (i.e., scientific research programmer/analyst), operations, and other support openings at NASA GISS through our contractor office, please contact
<a href="https://www.giss.nasa.gov/staff/jbarbara.html">
John Barbara</a>,
Autonomic Integra,
2880 Broadway,
New York, NY 10025.</p>



<h4>Internships</h4>

<p>Research internship positions at NASA GISS for high school and college students are managed through GISS's education office.
Many are summer positions that are part of the
<a href="/edu/ccri/">Climate Change Research Initiative</a>,
but there are also opportunities for autumn and spring semester internships.
Applicants for internships must be U.S. citizens. Depending on project requirements,
the intern may be required to reside in the NYC metro area or may be able to work remotely.
<br />
<a href="/edu/intern/">+ Read More</a></p>





<h4 class="goback">+ <a href="/about/">Return to About GISS</a></h4>



